    "This combination enables comprehensive fossil analysis and improved accuracy (Nasir et al. 2021).",
    "However, hybrid models increase computational and memory demands, leading to longer training times and requiring more powerful resources.",
    "Effective optimization and parameter tuning are essential to ensure the models work together efficiently.",
    "Diverse imaging modalities have been utilized for fossil characterization and analysis, ranging from conventional optical microscopy to high energy X-ray volume imaging, providing complementary insights into sample tomographic structure and composition.",
    "In this context, fossil imaging modalities refers to the various techniques used to capture detailed visual representations of fossils, allowing the study of their morphology and internal structures."
  ]
